INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760231727284', 'jlcd1', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Hicks) Great teacher, great course. The readings are all super interesting, even though they are confusing sometimes. Workload is not overly much. Assignments are really fun, only downside Dr. Hicks (who is a great teacher, and leads awesome discussions) is a really slow grader.', '2025-10-12T01:15:27.284Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760231672898', 'jlcd1', 5, NULL, 'Holy moly this class was amazing! Dr. Walker-Dale is an incredible instructor and leads very engaging discussions. She grades pretty easy but her feed back is to die for‚Ä¶ she writes entire pages for you and her feedback can be longer than what you actually wrote. Topics taught are quite unique (quantum theory, modernity, etc.) and you even get to lead class for a day (where you can cold call lol). HWD was helpful in office hours but she likes participation so participating a lot will help. Also readings were super long so I‚Äôd recommend that you start early on them. 11/10 and would 100% recommend! :D', '2025-10-12T01:14:32.898Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233445476', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Weil) [2025] Dr. Weil is a nice guy but I do have a bit of a bone to pick. Generally I found his discussions uninteresting and not super engaging, but take that as you may. My biggest pet peeve with Weil is that he‚Äôs very unclear with what he wants from you, and gives pretty confusing and un-constructive feedback. Best thing I can recommend if you‚Äôre struggling with that is to go to office hours and talk with him and get clear on his expectations. Just try and get through it as best you can. I will say that I found it hard to express opinions or go about work the way it made sense for me. He‚Äôs very strict about writing his way, understanding things his way, and doing things his way. The first few months were okay, but near the end of the semester I just felt tired and depleted. If you get him, you‚Äôll work through it, but if you can switch, I would suggest it.', '2025-10-12T01:44:05.476Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233441892', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Neemeh) [2024] Dr. Neemeh was great! They were super chill and good at handling fights and issues in the chat. They‚Äôre very respectful, especially if personal issues are interfering with your participation in the class. The discussions are interesting and civil, some of the most fun I‚Äôve had. They‚Äôre a bit of a harsh grader but are very good at giving clear and concise feedback to help you grow as a writer. Neemeh is the GOAT, would recommendüëç', '2025-10-12T01:44:01.892Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233436108', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Rees) [2025] bro dr rees is def the worst hns teacher. The class basically teaches you to have an open mind, but he has the opposite of an open mind, like he takes off points for not perfectly conforming to his vision of what a philosopher is. It is downright painful to try and make a logical argument during class, since he just bulldozes it down by totally ignoring it and forcing everyone to focus on what some dumb philosopher says. Like the whole point of hns is to learn how to think, but all dr rees teaches is how other philosophers think, there‚Äôs not much practice on thinking for yourself. Some parts of the class were inherently dumb, like the phrase ‚Äúhuman nature‚Äù (humans are so fricking diverse) or the fact that you get points taken off reading questions if you add some of your opinion to it (you just have to word vomit the opinions and badly formed arguments of some philosopher from the reading) and my friend got points taken off for some really dumb reasons, like not fully articulating an obvious idea. From what I can see, the only way to get an A in this class with this teacher is to either 1. Be a really good writer or 2. Read the readings cover to cover and essentially just answer each question in the most boring, obvious way. He also doesn‚Äôt read the chat. Which is a problem, obviously. Also don‚Äôt use the word ‚Äúsolid‚Äù in assignments, he can‚Äôt seem to comprehend that it has multiple meanings other than a stage of matter.', '2025-10-12T01:43:56.108Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233409996', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Rees) [2025] Dr. Rees is amazing. He grades easy, he is super nice, and the class is just very fun overall. The best part of HNS is randomly criticizing every single philosopher there is & debating about everything aggressively with classmates. And the readings‚Ä¶ uh if you don‚Äôt like the readings at first, you will at least definitely have better reading comprehension skills by the end of the class. Note for new students: don‚Äôt discuss off-topic stuff in the comments, even if it‚Äôs about philosophy too. Dr. Rees normally doesn‚Äôt watch the comments section because it‚Äôs a whirlwind of aggression and colorful speech bubbles, but you can tell sometimes he‚Äôs annoyed by it too lol', '2025-10-12T01:43:29.996Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO replies(id, review_id, author, text, created_at, poster_email, poster_sid) VALUES('rp_1760233420988', 'r_1760233409996', NULL, '^Well idk about that but I also got straight As so‚Ä¶ personal opinion i guess. Also, the class is NOT boring. At least for my class. It‚Äôs literally the least boring class there is and everything is so chaotic. You‚Äôll survive not being off-topic for a few minutes. Looking at the comments, did we even get the same teacher?', '2025-10-12T01:43:40.988Z'::timestamptz, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO replies(id, review_id, author, text, created_at, poster_email, poster_sid) VALUES('rp_1760233415948', 'r_1760233409996', NULL, '^bruh since when does he grade easy? I got almost straight As, but my buddy who is awesome at philosophy got like awful grades for dumb reasons.', '2025-10-12T01:43:35.948Z'::timestamptz, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233398627', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Rees)[2025] I really like the class, since it has a lot of different views that are fun to argue against. Totally recommended for anyone who loves arguing/debate/logic and will argue against almost every philosopher just because they can. Dr Rees is cool, but he grades kinda harsh, so make sure your writing is perfectly clear and you address every single part of the prompt.', '2025-10-12T01:43:18.627Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO replies(id, review_id, author, text, created_at, poster_email, poster_sid) VALUES('rp_1760233405141', 'r_1760233398627', NULL, '^I agree with everything above, except I wouldn‚Äôt recommend Dr. Rees for students who like to think for themselves. It‚Äôs incredibly aggravating. Spoken as someone who personally insulted most of the philosophers from the readings for valid reasons. HWD is the best teacher for this class.', '2025-10-12T01:43:25.141Z'::timestamptz, NULL, NULL) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233394412', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Neemeh) [2024] Pretty nice class! The readings can feel really long, but Dr. Neemeh spends a good amount of time explaining during class. My biggest concern is that we often have really long readings and have to submit reading questions before having class time to properly break down the reading. Honestly not too bad, it can be stressful at times, but as long as you take time to close read you can do pretty well.', '2025-10-12T01:43:14.412Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233386636', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Weil) [2023-2024] Meh class. A lot of him rambling about the material and making us summarize it in the discussion sections so it was kind of underwhelming. He gives a lot of feedback on assignments but 50% of it is ‚Äúelaborate on this.‚Äù He‚Äôs pretty helpful in office hours and responds to emails a lot but I usually went to office hours to figure out what he wanted me to write so most of the essays were really based on his conception of a ‚Äúgood paper‚Äù rather than an interesting thesis/content. Another really annoying aspect of his course is that he would ask us to participate in class and share our opinions about the reading but when we talked about our opinions he would criticize them so participation really went down at the end of the year. Also the reading questions due before class are super unhelpful since they are worth a decent portion of your grade and they are graded based on correctness. The problem is, they are done before class so there isn‚Äôt time to ask for help or let the material sink in. A decent amount of students were kinda stressed about the reading questions since some of the questions were cryptic and the readings were convoluted at times. I feel like the course causes more annoyance than stress but overall you are not missing out if you don‚Äôt take it. If you end up taking it I would recommend getting a different teacher to avoid boredom and annoyance. Might have been because I wasn‚Äôt really interested in what we were reading but the teacher didn‚Äôt help.', '2025-10-12T01:43:06.636Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233380220', 'jhns2', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Walker-Dale) [2023-2024] This class was great and really fun! Dr. HWD‚Äôs feedback on assignments was always the best and really helpful in the future.  I can tell that she took a careful and long time examining all my papers and definitely helped me understand this course well, because I was very shaky in the beginning.', '2025-10-12T01:43:00.220Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
