INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233931443', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Wallhagen) [2023-2024] - honestly dr. wallhagen is way overhated while he‚Äôs a strict grader, if you make sure to do the readings and go to his office hours, he really cares about making sure you understand the material and do as well as you can. The quizzes were definitely hard and required you to think about the material, but the writing assignments were super fun and so were jeopardy weeks!', '2025-10-12T01:52:11.443Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233926163', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Mare) Its basically just a stats class with very little bio or philosophy so if you‚Äôre into that it probably won‚Äôt be too bad. Personally, I was not a fan because it was sold to me as a philosophical bio class and I hated all the stats stuff. Dr. Mare is fine, talks pretty slow and monotone and can get sidetracked but he‚Äôs mostly chill. The only time I really didn‚Äôt like him was when I forgot to submit something and he absolutely ripped me to shreds in his comment on canvas.', '2025-10-12T01:52:06.163Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233922424', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Mare) I hated the class, dropped it for the second semester. The content was just really confusing and chaotic for me. The lectures were boring and VERY LONG. Mare isn‚Äôt too bad (he let me do finals corrections even after I dropped the course), I just dislike the course and how its setup, especially how topics are introduced.', '2025-10-12T01:52:02.424Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233919428', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr Neemeh) [2023-2024] I didn‚Äôt find the discussions in class super helpful since usually we just went over the same things that we learned in the lectures before class, and didn‚Äôt go much deeper than that. This deeper analysis would have been helpful since there were numerous quiz questions that were either on material that wasn‚Äôt explicitly taught, or required analysis of what was taught, but then you were never taught how to do that analysis. A lot of the exams and midterms had those sort of questions too, so I‚Äôm glad there were corrections. Definitely go to office hours or email if you have any questions since you can avoid getting docked points pretty easily that way.', '2025-10-12T01:51:59.428Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233916564', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr Wallhagen) [2023-2024] Super awesome teacher. Makes the class interesting and goes really in-depth with the material. You can tell he really enjoys teaching, and he brings that enthusiasm to his lectures. He challenges his students, which will definitely make yo+u a better learner, and he always makes sure to stay on a particular subject until the entire class understands it, not just the most advanced students. Also, he is willing to engage in discussions with students and gets super interested in what they have to say, even if it‚Äôs not entirely related to the subject of discussion (for example if you have an insight about the material and want to share it, many times it will turn into a class-wide discussion). In my experience, his grading is extremely lenient on writing assignments, but very strict on the short answer sections of the exams.', '2025-10-12T01:51:56.564Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233912525', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Neemeh) [2023-2024] Super helpful MSB teacher! The course itself was not too bad but the stats were a little confusing as that was totally a new field for me. Dr. Neemeh was a great teacher though and helped me to understand the material. As long as you watch the lectures before class (very important to do!!) then the class will make sense. The course workload wasnt too much but for writing assignments definitely dont wait until last minute in case you need help on answering some of the questions (as Dr. Neemeh doesnt usually answer emails over weekends). He was helpful in office hours and lets you run ideas by him to let you know if you are on the right track. Also not a mean grader! As long as you put in the work and show an understanding of the material, its not hard to get an A (this is for things like the writing assignments). The exams in this class are a little challenging but as long as you understand the material you will be fine. The exams are open note so they wont ask simple definition questions and will require you to be well versed in the subject. But dont let that discourage you!!! Just make sure to always watch the lectures before class and if you are struggling with something then go to office hours. If you do this then you will be just fine. There were, at least this year, corrections for the exams that will give you up to half points back. Dr. Neemeh is a pretty fair and lenient grader on exams. Overall great teacher but MSB was not my favorite course. (Though not hard to finish with a strong A as long as you put in the work :))!', '2025-10-12T01:51:52.525Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233907380', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Tillman) Dr Tillman is nice and his tangents where kinda funny, but honestly they didn‚Äôt really help me understand the topic. The lectures are really important because not everything covered in the lectures is covered in class, and the weekly quizzes are on the content covered in the lectures. The quizzes are kinda confusing, as they are more focused on applying what we learned in the lectures, not showing that you watched them. The midterms/finals and essays were weird, and I usually got worse grades than I was expecting tbh.', '2025-10-12T01:51:47.380Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233903740', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, 'Tillman is a great teacher but has hneemehigh specific standards, but is fair and a good teacher', '2025-10-12T01:51:43.740Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233900188', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr Tillman) Definitely the best MSB teacher. Is very engaging and willing to explain material. His classes are honestly really fun and enjoyable, and he is good about having review', '2025-10-12T01:51:40.188Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233894564', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, 'I also agree that Neemeh is the best MSB instructor. They made sure the class was engaging and fun, and never made me feel stupid. Neemeh also had a thing with checking up with some students before class started, and idk I thought that was super helpful with making the environment less stressful. If someone had a question they made sure to let us know that OH was always open for us, or we could ask in class. I do not recommend emailing them because they take an eternity to respond, so PLEASE take into consideration the OH or in class questions seriously! But I definitely recommend Dr. Neemeh as a core instructor for those who were wondering :D', '2025-10-12T01:51:34.564Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233890940', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr Neemeh) [2024-2025] Dr. Neemeh is an AMAZING teacher. They teach clearly, concisely and is super kind, so if you need any help on a quiz, an assignment, or even just to chat, Dr. Neemeh is there for you in office hours! I learnt so much in MSB and was amazed by how they explained things. A tip I have for this course is to write notes during class, as it is super helpful for the weekly quizzes. If you have any questions, ask Dr. Neemeh because you want to make sure that you understand each concept. The class environment is super chill and not stressful at all! Overall, amazing course, amazing teacher.', '2025-10-12T01:51:30.940Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233887628', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, 'Dr. Neehmeh was a good teacher and a fair grader, you could easily tell what they wanted if you got points taken off. My only complaint is that they were not always the fastest to answer emails and office hours. Other than that it was a great year.', '2025-10-12T01:51:27.628Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233884692', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr Neemeh) [2023-2024] Probably the best MSB teacher ngl.', '2025-10-12T01:51:24.692Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO reviews(id, course_id, rating, author, text, created_at, status, poster_email, poster_sid, upvotes, downvotes) VALUES('r_1760233880100', 'omsb9', NULL, NULL, '(Dr. Wallhagen) [2023-2024] Amazing at helping you understand a topic if you ask the right questions, you can‚Äôt expect everything to be spoon-fed to you so if you have questions in his class ASK. He is quite a specific and harsh grader at times which can be difficult to cope with. Also if you are doing an assignment BE AS SPECIFIC AS POSSIBLE. He isn‚Äôt really as bad as a teacher that everyone makes him seem to be, but if you are fragile about grades and don‚Äôt think you can handle learning from mistakes probably go for another section. (I agree)', '2025-10-12T01:51:20.100Z'::timestamptz, 'published', NULL, NULL, 0, 0) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
